  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 21-24.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - The first interruption to the record of Caleb's posterity is now occasioned by a resumed reference to ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Hezron",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", who at the age of threescore took to wife (as it seems from ver. 24) ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Abiah",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", sister to Gilead, daughter of the eminent man ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Machir",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", who was Manasseh's oldest son by an Aramitess concubine (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 7:14",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "). Two sons of Hezron by Abiah are given (the latter of them a posthumous child), but the elder having a son called ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Jair",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " tracked, no doubt as one who became famous by the number of cities he took. He was thus connected on the father's side with a great family of Judah, and on the mother's with a great family of Manasseh. He is probably not the Jair of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Judges 10:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", with his \"thirty sons, thirty ass colts, and thirty cities.\" And ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "יָאִיר",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greek",
        "text": "Ἰάειζος",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Mark 5:22",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") is not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "hebrew",
        "text": "יָעִיד",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "2 Samuel 21:19",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 Chronicles 20:5",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". Evident stress is laid on his maternal descent. Thus (",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Numbers 32:41",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ") he is styled son of Manasseh, and hence also the explanation of the last clause of ver. 23, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
